<p>If you took CS 111, you used Canopy as your editor. Canopy had a file editor area and a <b>console</b> (also known as a <b>shell</b>) 
In CS 210, we are using cloud 9 as the editor and the <b>chrome browser</b> for its console, where you can evaluate single JavaScript expressions and test your code for outputs.</p>

<p>To get to the console on a mac:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Open up a chrome browser (any website will do)</li>
  <li>On the top bar, go to view --> developer --> JavaScript Console</li>
</ol>


